<subSubSection id="C32E6525FFD5FF95FF49FB25FBCB8D7B" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8B36AEFFD5FF95FF49FB25FBCB8D7B" blockId="4.[143,654,1218,1744]" lastBlockId="4.[685,1196,788,1046]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">
DIAGNOSIS: The addition of a new species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D2DFFD5FF95FF61FAC7FF168C5C" authorityName="Mcdonald" authorityYear="1981" box="[143,215,1308,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Aleixus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940EABCFFD5FF95FF61FAC7FF168C5C" box="[143,215,1308,1329]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Aleixus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
requires a rearrangement in the generic diagnosis as given by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA54B5FFFD5FF95FE8EFAE2FD4C8C22" author="Rolston and McDonald" box="[352,653,1337,1359]" firstAuthor="Rolston" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the New York Entomogical Society" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" pagination="257 - 272" part="88" refId="ref7456" refString="Rolston, L. H. and F. J. D. McDonald. 1981. Conspectus of the Pentatomini genera of the Western Hemisphere - part 2 (Hemiptera: Pentatomidae). Journal of the New York Entomogical Society 88: 257 - 272." title="Conspectus of the Pentatomini genera of the Western Hemisphere - part 2 (Hemiptera: Pentatomidae)" type="journal article" year="1981">Rolston and McDonald (1981)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA54B5FFFD5FF95FF54FA8CFEF88C00" author="Rider" box="[186,313,1367,1389]" firstAuthor="Rider" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the New York Entomological Society" pageId="4" pageNumber="255" pagination="193 - 221" part="102" refId="ref7266" refString="Rider, D. A. 1994. A generic conspectus of the tribe Procleticini Pennington (Heteroptera, Pentatomidae), with the description of Paraodmalea rubella, new genus and species. Journal of the New York Entomological Society 102: 193 - 221." title="A generic conspectus of the tribe Procleticini Pennington (Heteroptera, Pentatomidae), with the description of Paraodmalea rubella, new genus and species" type="journal article" year="1994">Rider (1994)</bibRefCitation>
. Head: distinctly declivent at apex; antennal segment Inot reaching apex of head; antennal segment II and III cylindrical, segments IV and Vsomewhat inflated; antennal segment II longer than any other segment; juga surpassing clypeus, obtuse at apex, not contiguous anteriorly. Rostrum reaching metacoxae. 
<emphasis id="B940EABCFFD5FF95FE20F9D2FDDD8F72" bold="true" box="[462,540,1545,1567]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Thorax:</emphasis>
Pronotum with humeral angles with large tubercles, dorsally bifid and black at apices; tubercles ventral surface bearing a short blunt projection. Scutellum subtriangular, apex broadly rounded not reaching apices of coria. Thoracic sterna nearly flat. Peritreme acuminate apically, extending at least beyond middle of evaporatorium. 
<emphasis id="B940EABCFFD5FF95FC5DFCCEFC208A47" box="[947,993,789,810]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Legs</emphasis>
: with dorsal surface of femora produced distally. 
<emphasis id="B940EABCFFD5FF95FC3FFCEAFBF28A2A" bold="true" box="[977,1075,817,839]" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Abdominal spine small, not reaching between metacoxae. Characters used as diagnostic to the genus and found to be variable between the two species include length of the humeral angles, development of the tooth placed distally in the femora, length of the peritrema, and shape of tibia (see also comments in the description of the new species).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
